E4DvPYXO4rg.title: Walmart's Partnership With Acres for America Makes Lasting Impact
E4DvPYXO4rg.description:
For 20 years, Walmart has partnered with the National Fish and Wildlife Foundation on the Acres for America program, helping protect over 2 million acres of critical land across the U.S. When the program started, the idea was to protect 1 acre of land for every 1 acre Walmart built on. Today it‚Äôs evolved to about 20-1! 
 
Acres for America has preserved ecosystems, bolstered biodiversity, safeguarded clean water, and created recreational spaces for the benefit of both people and wildlife. And we recently shared the exciting news that we've renewed the program for 10 more years, with a $34.5 million pledge. 
 
In this episode of the Huddle, Chris West from NFWF and Jen Barnhouse from The Nature Conservancy joined me at the Kings River Preserve, a beautiful 5,000 acre preserve in Northwest Arkansas. We talked about the widespread impact of the Acres for America program, and how conservation isn‚Äôt just about protecting beautiful places‚Äîit‚Äôs also about sustaining natural resources for future generations. 
 
You'll also hear how anyone can support this work, either through small actions like rounding up a purchase or by finding ways to connect with local conservation initiatives. Whether you‚Äôre passionate about the environment, want to leave a legacy for future generations, or simply enjoy outdoor recreation, this episode is for you! 

Save Money. Live Better.

C1gsH0V8fFc.title: Serving Those Who Serve
C1gsH0V8fFc.description:
Monday is Veterans Day, one of the most special days of the year. At Walmart we‚Äôre so grateful to those who serve or have served in the military, and we support them however we can. A big way is through employment. We‚Äôre proud to have hired 400,000 veterans since 2013. Another way is through the products we sell. 
 
This week I recorded a Huddle episode with Mark Doyle, whose company ‚Äì Rags of Honor Brands ‚Äì makes military-themed shirts we sell in stores and online. We talked about his story of starting Rags of Honor to provide jobs and support to veterans, and how working with Walmart has helped his company do even more. We're proud to partner with Rags of Honor as they serve those who have served all of us ‚Äì and I know you‚Äôll be inspired by Mark's mission-driven mindset and willingness to take action. 
 
Please join me in thanking all the brave men and women who have worn the uniform and allowed us to live freely in this country. Let‚Äôs all honor them today and every day. Full episode here: bit.ly/3gxON5F

9DfKbUr8Xh8.title: Prescription for Service: Plus, A Surprise Promotion!
9DfKbUr8Xh8.description:
It‚Äôs #AmericanPharmacistsMonth, and I had the chance to sit down with Obi Odi, one of our pharmacists at Store #4487 in Aiken, South Carolina. Obi‚Äôs journey is remarkable. Originally from Nigeria, Obi came to the U.S. to further his education and pursue a career in pharmacy. While studying, he was deeply impacted by the events of 9/11 and decided to pause his education to serve in the U.S. Marine Corps, even though he was about to graduate! After completing that Military service, he finished his pharmacy degree and found an opportunity to continue serving his community as a pharmacist at Walmart.¬†¬†
¬†¬†
In this episode of The Huddle, Obi shares how his role as a pharmacist allows him to connect with customers beyond their prescriptions, extending a helping hand to those who might need it most. His approach to service‚Äîwhether in the Military or in the pharmacy‚Äîhas always been about stepping up for others.¬†¬†
¬†¬†
Obi embodies Walmart‚Äôs core values of service, respect, excellence, and integrity in everything he does, and it was my absolute honor to offer him a well-deserved promotion to Pharmacy Manager. We‚Äôre thankful for Obi‚Äôs service and proud to have so many incredible pharmacists on #TeamWalmart. You don‚Äôt want to miss this inspiring episode!
Save Money. Live Better.

yXTkIyO5oPQ.title: Growing Together! Seller Success on Walmart Marketplace
yXTkIyO5oPQ.description:
We‚Äôve had an exciting week in San Francisco, California, where we just wrapped up our Let's Grow! 2024 Walmart Marketplace Seller Summit for small businesses, inventors, and other sellers interested in joining our Walmart.com Marketplace. Marketplace allows us to offer customers hundreds of millions more items than we sell in our stores! 

For this edition of the Huddle, I talked with Bill Pond, CEO of RTIC Outdoors. RTIC is a digitally-native brand that makes premium products like coolers and cups. They first partnered with Walmart by joining our Marketplace. As you‚Äôll hear Bill explain in this episode, that led to more sales and more customers for RTIC, then eventually having their products inside our U.S. stores. Today RTIC‚Äôs products are sold both in our stores AND our Marketplace, and the two perfectly compliment each other.    

It was especially fun to record this episode inside Walmart Store 100, which is where I started my Walmart career 31 years ago. So much has changed since then ‚Äì particularly the opportunities we now have to sell many more items and fulfill many more orders in many more ways. But what hasn‚Äôt changed? We‚Äôre still so proud to welcome new sellers with new products, and help them grow WITH us.

Then there are people like Anjie Robertson and myself who started with Walmart and saw it turn into a rewarding career. I met Anjie a couple months ago at our Manager Academy, where she shared she couldn‚Äôt attend the Associates Week she was invited to 15 years ago, because of being promoted. Anjie politely asked if she could come this year, to one of the biggest and best family reunions and celebrations in the world! 

Anjie joined me for this episode of The Huddle, just after joining me on stage at our U.S. Associates meeting! We talked about her 30-year career with Walmart, how her experiences have shaped her people-centered approach to management, the importance of meeting people where they are, and what it truly means to go "all in.‚Äù We also talked about the memorable moment where Anjie recommended we begin an annual bonus program for our store associates. (Spoiler alert: we listen!) 

Anjie is an incredible associate with a magnetic personality, and her story shows what's possible when you take risks, believe in yourself, and go "all in" on your goals. I'm proud of Anjie for asking to come to Associates Week this year and I'm excited for you to hear her story in this episode. You won't want to miss it!

BqyhgsBOows.title: Grand Opening Celebration!
BqyhgsBOows.description:
Yesterday, we celebrated the grand opening of Store 8861, our brand-new Walmart Neighborhood Market in Santa Rosa Beach, Florida! üéâ A grand opening is always filled with excitement, and this one was particularly special. It represents the first of the 150 new stores we're planning to build or convert in the next five years along with our ongoing efforts to remodel hundreds of our existing stores to better serve our customers. 
 
In this episode of The Huddle, I had the pleasure to chat with Brandon, the Store Manager, at this beautiful new location. His journey with Walmart has been truly inspiring. When he was a Support Manager, he had the opportunity to assist in opening a new store in Gulfport, Mississippi, and has dreamt of opening a store as a Store Manager ever since. Today, he is living that dream and is thrilled to serve the Santa Rosa community! We talked about the unique aspects of this new store, including its proximity to the beach and the capacity to cater to both locals and tourists with a larger square footage, extensive assortment, and standout pharmacy. We also talked about all the amazing long-term associates who have transferred from other stores to support this new location, bringing a wealth of experience to help the new team thrive. 
 
We're thrilled to bring nearly 100 new jobs to the area and look forward to providing outstanding service to all of our customers on Florida‚Äôs Gulf Coast. Whether you're a local or visiting over the summer, we'd love to have you stop by and check out our new store!

I started working with¬†Walmart¬†when I was in school. I was just hoping to earn some money for the summer ‚Äî but I soon realized that working in a store taught me many things I couldn‚Äôt have learned in a classroom. Real-world work experience is crucial, and that‚Äôs why we're proud to be a partner of the¬†NRF Foundation's RISE Up program. RISE Up has helped 40,000 learners learn about and experience the retail industry, and build foundational employability skills.¬†

In this episode of The Huddle, I'm joined by John Marschhausen and Lori Messi from¬†Dublin City Schools¬†in Ohio, who were recognized by the Foundation for the amazing work they're doing immersing students from their district into local retailers. They have great advice for how organizations and institutions can take smart risks, engage with their communities, and build partnerships to change young people‚Äôs lives. The work happening in Dublin showcases what's possible when we invest in the future leaders of tomorrow. I'm excited to see the next generation ‚ÄúRISE Up‚Äù!

-YmtWTVuUdg.title: We're in it to Win it: John and Doug Talk Splitting Walmart Stock
-YmtWTVuUdg.description:
We just wrapped up an amazing Year Beginning Meeting in Houston! Yesterday, our CEO Doug McMillon closed out YBM by splitting Walmart‚Äôs stock for the first time since 1999! Doug joined me on The Huddle to discuss this exciting news ‚Äì what it means, and how it will allow even more people to become shareholders in our company. 
  
Of course, we also talked about our favorite group of Walmart shareholders: the 400,000 associates who own Walmart stock ‚Äì many who buy it through our Associate Stock Purchase benefit program. I joined that program my very first day in 1993. Sam Walton once called it ‚Äúthe single best thing we ever did.‚Äù 
  
Our associates act like owners every day, and we‚Äôre delighted at how many truly ARE owners of the company because they own stock. And we‚Äôre so excited to think of what‚Äôs ahead for all of us as we keep serving more customers and growing our company.

ddWlYGsulM8.title: They Said Yes!
ddWlYGsulM8.description:
As #VeteransDay approaches, I urge everyone to pause and appreciate the men and women who have served so bravely and selflessly to protect our country and freedoms. At Walmart, our commitment to supporting America‚Äôs Veterans and their families runs deep. We‚Äôre proud to have hired over 550,000 members of the military community over the last decade. 
 
Some of our newest Veteran associates have come through our Corporate Fellowship Program (CFP), which provides an innovative, 12-week experience that equips transitioning service members with professional training and hands-on learning to prepare for meaningful civilian careers. For this episode of The Huddle, I had the pleasure of talking with two current fellows ‚Äì Juli and Quintin Plank. We talked about their experiences in the military, their journey to becoming part of the Walmart CFP, and their advice to other Veterans navigating to civilian life. 
 
Best of all? I was thrilled to surprise both Juli and Quintin with official offer letters to become Walmart associates! We can‚Äôt wait for them to be part of our #WalmartFamily for many years to come. Happy #VeteransDay, to Juli, Quintin and all who have served. We can‚Äôt thank you enough! https://bit.ly/3gxON5F

qP7BRiGezQ8.title: Supporting U.S. Manufacturing
qP7BRiGezQ8.description:
As #NationalManufacturingDay approaches this Friday, we're proud to recognize the manufacturers behind Walmart products, who play a pivotal role in creating opportunities for our communities and workforce. Kent International Inc. is a great example of this. They've assembled millions of bikes at their South Carolina factory, including Walmart's Ozark Trail mountain bike line, and have been instrumental in revitalizing bicycle manufacturing in the U.S.

In this episode of The Huddle, I join Arnold Kamler, CEO of Kent International Inc., at their Manning, SC factory to talk about his journey working with Walmart and how they've evolved our Ozark Trail line. Arnold also shares valuable advice for anyone considering establishing manufacturing assembly in the U.S.

When I was a kid, my first bike was from Walmart ‚Äì and I know many of our customers got their start cycling the same way. As you shop for the holidays, consider checking out Ozark Trail bikes, knowing the significant impact each one has on people right here in the United States. https://bit.ly/3gxON5F

qvz7t4pDccc.title: The Huddle with Emmanuel Isiko
qvz7t4pDccc.description:
As we celebrate Driver and Tech Appreciation Week, I want to recognize our amazing associates in Walmart's Private Fleet who play a crucial role in keeping our stores stocked, and serving our partners and customers all over the country. I also want to shine a spotlight on Emmanuel - not only is he one of our great drivers, but he's also an amazing person whose story is the true embodiment of the American dream. Originally from Uganda, Emmanuel came to the U.S. 27 years ago to support his family back home. Despite the struggle to make ends meet and being encouraged to file for bankruptcy, he joined Walmart's private fleet in 2021 ‚Äì and it changed everything. Our Walmart U.S. team is honored to serve this great country, and one of the most impactful ways we do that is selling products that come from this country. We‚Äôre proud that about 2/3rds of our product spend is on items made, grown or assembled in the U.S.

MG-wCGqhGqM.title: A New Start in Chesapeake
MG-wCGqhGqM.description:
Someone once told me ‚Äúyour leadership is defined during the toughest times.‚Äù No one exemplifies that more than Alycia Mixon, the manager of Store 1841 in Chesapeake, VA. I met Alycia last November, under the most difficult circumstances imaginable ‚Äì after losing 6 members of the Walmart family.

Alycia‚Äôs first instinct was to step up for her people in a way that few others could. When I first saw her, she was standing on a chair, speaking to her team with the perfect balance of confidence and compassion. I visited 1841 last week, just as they started welcoming back customers, and it was great to see Alycia bringing her team into a new era for the store. For this episode of the Huddle, I talked with Alycia about how she‚Äôs continued to comfort and lead her team these past five months as they worked to remodel the store, build an outdoor memorial and reopen.

We‚Äôre committed to helping everyone at 1841 move forward, even as we continue to mourn the loss of six beautiful lives: Randy, Jesus, Lorenzo, Kellie, Brian, and Tyneka. And we‚Äôre so thankful for Alycia, who in the toughest of times, showed us what leadership looks like.

I recently had the pleasure of touring Ol√©‚Äôs Texas facilities and talking with Veronica and her son Edgar about the Ol√© story, and how they‚Äôre continuing to expand and invest. 

Walmart is passionate about supporting American entrepreneurs and businesses. This week, we held our ninth annual Open Call where more than 1,100 businesses from across the country pitched their products for a chance to see them on store shelves, Walmart.com, or our Walmart Marketplace. And we‚Äôve pledged to spend an additional $350 billion over the next 10 years on products made, grown, or assembled in the U.S. That investment will support the creation of an estimated 750,000 new U.S. jobs. 

It‚Äôs amazing to think of the difference we can make for so many lives by buying and selling products that support American jobs. I hope you‚Äôll join me in reflecting on that this weekend as we celebrate our nation‚Äôs 246th birthday. Happy Fourth of July and thank you!

hmddidPSY9E.title: Valentine‚Äôs Day Cookie Pizza with Homemade Strawberry Milk | Chow Down with Walmart
hmddidPSY9E.description:
Get ready for a Valentine‚Äôs showstopper that‚Äôs perfect for your special someone, the kids, even a Galentine‚Äôs Day party! It‚Äôs a Valentine‚Äôs Day cookie pizza & homemade strawberry milk. Chow Down chef Carolina Gelen shows you how to make this perfect combination of rich, chocolatey goodness & delicious, fruity freshness. Decorate the cookie pizza with the kids or the gals‚Äîhave fun with it, we promise it‚Äôs going to look great! For more recipes that will wow your loved ones, like & subscribe.

Get ingredients for this recipe: https://walmrt.us/3rptCLg
Follow Carolina on Instagram at @carolinagelen

Valentine‚Äôs Day cookie pizza ingredients:
(Makes 1) 

1 roll refrigerated chocolate chip cookie dough
Flour for dusting 
Marshmallow Fluff (about half of a 7.5 oz container)
Red, white, & pink candy-coated chocolates
Heart sprinkles 
1/2 cup hot fudge

Instructions:
1) Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.  Flip your sheet tray upside down so that it is a flat surface without a lip, then line it with parchment paper. 
2) Dust surface with flour.  Divide stick of dough into 2 pieces, one that is approximately 2/3 of the stick, & the remaining piece (about 1/3 of the stick). Using your hands, start pressing the pieces into the two sides of a heart, with the larger piece making the pointed base.  Once you have a basic heart shape, gently use your rolling pin to flatten the dough, reshaping with your hands when necessary.  Keep rolling the dough down until it is about 1/2 inch thick.  It‚Äôs okay if the shape is a little rustic looking.
3) Gently transfer dough to a sheet tray lined with parchment paper & bake for 15-18 minutes or until golden brown. 
4) Once removed from the oven, reshape the heart with a knife by trimming the edges of the cookie while cookie is still hot. Let cool thoroughly.
5) Spread Marshmallow Fluff over the cookie, as if icing a cake, creating a base layer on the pizza cookie.  
6) Top with candy-coated chocolates & heart sprinkles, or any sprinkles & candies your heart desires.
7) Heat hot fudge per package directions, then mix with a teaspoon of water at a time until you can easily drizzle it with a spoon.  Drizzle hot fudge over cookie pizza & serve.

Strawberry milk ingredients:
(Makes 1) 
16 oz strawberries (fresh or frozen), quartered
3/4 cup granulated sugar
2/3 cup water
Milk (can be non-dairy if desired)
Marshmallow Fluff for the rim (optional) 
Heart sprinkles for the rim (optional)
 
Instructions:
1) Combine strawberries, sugar, & water in a saucepan over medium heat.  Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until slightly thickened. Turn off the heat.
2) Transfer strawberry mixture carefully into a blender, taking care to avoid splashes. Place lid on blender, then remove the center cap from lid. Cover the hole with a towel.  Holding the towel in place with your hand, blend thoroughly. Transfer to a container & refrigerate until cold.
3) Dip the rim of your serving glass into Marshmallow Fluff, then dip into a shallow plate of sprinkles. Fill serving glass about 2/3 full with milk, then add strawberry syrup slowly, stirring to incorporate, until you‚Äôve reached the desired color & taste.

OvW6rYvsiBw.description:
Want a healthy, satisfying breakfast but don‚Äôt have the time? We‚Äôve got the goods: delicious egg muffins & granola smoothies you can make ahead to grab & go in the AM. Chow Down chef Ali shows you how to cook 10 eggs at once, with your favorite toppings‚Äîor whatever leftovers you have in the fridge! They go perfectly with a refreshing blueberry granola smoothie (also make-ahead), packed with yogurt, nut butter, & fruit. Breakfast couldn‚Äôt get any easier with these two recipes. Egg Muffin Ingredients 

Egg Muffin Base (makes 12) 
10 eggs
1/4 cup milk
1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese
1 tsp. salt

Tex-Mex Filling
Leftover or cooked taco meat
Orange bell pepper, diced 
Shredded cheese 
Sliced jalape√±o (optional)

Bacon & Cheese Filling
Leftover or cooked bacon, in bite-size pieces
Shredded cheese  

Ham & Potato Filling
Cooked potatoes or hash browns, in bite-size pieces 
Ham, in bite-size pieces
Chopped chives (optional) 

Vegetable Filling
Roasted red peppers or cooked vegetables
Orange bell pepper, diced
Spinach or a leafy green
Shredded cheese 

Egg Muffin Instructions:
1) Preheat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.  Line a 12-muffin tin with paper liners.
2) Combine base ingredients & whisk together, ensuring that they are well-blended.
3) Fill each muffin liner with your fillings of choice.  You can use leftovers, or you can cut up fresh vegetables‚Äîmake it your own! Make sure fillings are bite-sized. If they are fresh vegetables, use softer vegetables, or pre-cook them.
4) Pour egg mixture over the fillings until it reaches near the top of the liners.  Bake until set, about 20-25 minutes.

Granola Smoothie Ingredients (makes 1) 

1/4 cup Greek yogurt
2 Tbsp. nut butter
1/4 cup granola
3 tsp. cranberries
1/2 cup blueberries
1/2 banana, sliced
1/2 to 3/4 cup milk, for blending (feel free to substitute with almond milk, oat milk, or any other non-dairy milk)

Granola Smoothie Instructions:
1) Place all the ingredients except for the milk in a zip top bag.  Seal the bag & freeze it overnight, up to 3 months. 
2) When ready to eat, empty contents of bag into blender & add milk, blending to desired consistency.

7tJE7W7a90Y.title: Make the Tastiest White Chocolate Eggnog Fondue | Chow Down with Walmart
7tJE7W7a90Y.description:
Eggnog = holidays! Chef Jordan Andino has a recipe that turns a perfect holiday drink into a showstopping dessert: this amazing White Chocolate Eggnog Fondue! It goes with everything from gingerbread cookies to dried apricots, to even pretzels. It's an impressive yet easy dessert that'll have everyone gathering around to get a piece! Don't forget to like & subscribe for even more recipes the fam will love. 

Get ingredients for the recipe: https://walmrt.us/3y3IX5J

Follow Chef Jordan Andino on Instagram @fork_knife 

White Chocolate Eggnog Fondue Ingredients
1 cup eggnog
1/4 cup heavy cream
1/4 tsp. salt
1/4 tsp. nutmeg
1 Tbsp. brandy or rum (can be substituted with water or heavy cream)
1/2 tsp. cornstarch
1 cup (6 oz) white chocolate chips 

Dippers:
Strawberries
Pretzel rods
Gingerbread cookies
Pound cake
Apple
Dried mango 
Dried apricots


Instructions:
1) Over medium heat, combine eggnog, cream, nutmeg, & salt in a small saucepan & bring to a simmer
2) In a small bowl, whisk together brandy or rum & cornstarch to make a slurry (can use water or heavy cream for an alcohol-free option)
3) Pour slurry into cream mixture & whisk until thickened, about 30 seconds
4) Remove pan from heat & gradually whisk in white chocolate until smooth 
5) Serve warm with gingerbread cookies, pretzel sticks, strawberries, pound cake, apple, dried fruit, & any other dippers you desire
6) If fondue gets too thick after serving, reheat in the microwave for 15-30 seconds in a microwave-safe container, or reheat in an oven at 300¬∞F degrees for 5 minutes using an oven-safe container‚Äã

PFLqYPe3Y_4.title: Make the Best Halloween Rocky Road & Witches‚Äô Brew Iced Tea | Chow Down with Walmart ‚Äã
PFLqYPe3Y_4.description:
Halloween Rocky Road is the ultimate DIY candy bar. Turn all the candy in your house into a treat that‚Äôs impressive & delicious. Pair it with Witches‚Äô Brew, a color-changing drink that is the perfect trick to go with this yummy & easy treat. Enjoy this scary good combo, & don‚Äôt forget to like & subscribe for more delicious recipes.

Get ingredients for both recipes: https://walmrt.us/3acr1uJ

Witches‚Äô Brew Iced Tea ingredients:
2 Tbsp. dried butterfly pea flowers
2 cups boiling water 
Crushed ice 
2 oz simple syrup 
Juice of 2-3 lemons 

Instructions:
1. In a liquid measuring cup, add dried butterfly pea flowers. Pour boiling water over the flowers, stir, & set aside to steep for 5-7 minutes or until the liquid is deep blue. 
2. Using a slotted spoon, remove soaked flowers from the liquid & refrigerate to cool. 
3. Fill a tall glass with crushed ice. 
4. Fill half the glass with cooled butterfly tea.
5. Add simple syrup. 
6. Finish with lemon juice & stir.

Halloween Rocky Road ingredients:
(Makes 16 bars)
Nonstick cooking spray
1 12 oz package semi sweet chocolate chips
1 stick butter, unsalted 
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 cup roasted peanuts
1 cup mini marshmallows 
2 Twix bars, each bar cut into 4 pieces

Toppings:
M&Ms
Halloween sprinkles 
Candy eyeballs 
Gummy worms 
Candy corn

Instructions:
1. Spray a 9x9‚Äù baking pan with nonstick cooking spray, then line with parchment paper. 
2. Combine chocolate chips, butter & salt in a glass bowl & microwave in 30-second intervals, gently folding together until melted & combined. 
3. Fold peanuts, marshmallows, & Twix pieces into melted chocolate. (Peanuts can be excluded if desired.)
4. Pour chocolate mixture into baking pan & spread in an even layer. 
5. Top with M&M‚Äôs, Halloween sprinkles, candy corn, candy eyeballs, & gummy worms (or your choice of candy). 
6. Refrigerate for 2 hours. 
7. Cut into 16 bars (4x4) & serve. 

Subscribe for more Chow Down recipes here: https://walmrt.us/2YiCHtg
Follow Chow Down host Sam on Instagram: @samanthaseneviratne

E3DfpXpotX0.title: Never Forget
E3DfpXpotX0.description: Today marks 20 years since the attacks of September 11th. John Furner was a Store Manager in Jacksonville, NC, and distinctly remembers sharing the news with his team - several of which had family members and loved ones serving in the military. In that same moment, Dan Bartlett was with President George W. Bush. Dan is our EVP of Corporate Affairs and came to Walmart after a career in government as Communications Director and Counselor to the President. Dan joined The Huddle to talk about the events of that day - from first hearing the news to conversations had on Air Force One to standing in the Oval Office as President Bush addressed the nation. Our country was forever changed September 11, 2001, but we have stayed resilient and learned to rely on each other and support one another. Please take a moment to remember the 2,977 men, women and children killed that day and to honor the brave first responders who ran toward danger to save others. Two decades ago, we made a promise never to forget. Let us recommit ourselves to fulfilling it together.

h6NvjyP7k4g.title: One Pan Shrimp Tacos | Chow Down with Walmart ‚Äã
h6NvjyP7k4g.description:
These shrimp tacos taste amazing‚Äîsweet, salty, & smoky. You know what‚Äôs even better? They‚Äôre all cooked in one pan in under 20 minutes. With the craziness of back to school time, these quick, easy, & customizable tacos are your go to! Subscribe to Chow Down to get all the recipes your family will love! 

Ingredients:
1.5 lbs large shrimp, peeled & deveined
2 cups fresh pineapple, sliced into wedges
2 Tbsp. chipotle powder
2 tsp. sugar
2 tsp. salt (divided)
2 limes 
2 Tbsp. olive oil
1/4 tsp. red pepper flakes, optional
10-12 white corn tortillas

Garnish:
1 small red onion, sliced thin
1 avocado, sliced
1 jalape√±o, thinly sliced
1 cup crumbled cotija cheese
Lime wedges
Cilantro sprigs
Hot sauce, optional

Get ingredients: https://walmrt.us/2Vjy6pg

Instructions:
1. Preheat the broiler in your oven & position an oven rack on the level below. Line a sheet tray with aluminum foil. 

2. In a bowl, combine chipotle powder, sugar, 1.5 teaspoon salt, red pepper flakes, & olive oil. Add in zest from one lime & juice from half a lime, & whisk. Add shrimp to marinade & toss to coat evenly. 

3. Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt to pineapple & mix.

4. Coat sheet tray with cooking spray. Add marinated shrimp to the left half of the sheet tray, leaving space for the pineapple on the right. Spread salted pineapple evenly on the other half of the tray.

5. Place back under the broiler for 5-6 minutes, or until shrimp is cooked through & pineapple caramelized. 

6. On a medium-high flame, toast corn tortillas & fold inside a cloth napkin to keep warm. 

7. Build tacos with shrimp & pineapple. Garnish with sliced avocado, sliced red onion, thinly sliced jalape√±o, cotija cheese, cilantro sprigs, hot sauce, & a squeeze of lime.

Don't forget to like & subscribe for more Chow Down recipes: https://walmrt.us/3C9FnsD

zYjLJu6B7MM.title: 3 Fresh Fruit Popsicle Recipes | Chow Down with Walmart ‚Äã
zYjLJu6B7MM.description:
Looking for the perfect summer treat to cool you down? These delicious & colorful fresh fruit popsicles are the way to go! Check out our fruit combos or use whatever you have in the house & find yourself with a snack that the whole family will fight over! Love it? Hit subscribe for more Chow Down goodness!

Ingredients‚Äã:
Homemade Lemonade 
1 cup granulated sugar
1 cup water
3/4 cups lemon juice
3 cups cold water 

Fruit Medley Popsicles
6 strawberries, hulled & sliced thin lengthwise
2 kiwis, peeled, halved, & sliced thin
1 peach, cut into thin slices
1/2 cup blueberries

Tropical Fresh Fruit Popsicles
1/2 cup pineapple, thinly sliced into wedges 
1/2 mango, peeled & sliced thin lengthwise
1/2 cup honeydew melon, thinly sliced

Berry Lover Popsicles
8 strawberries, hulled & sliced thin lengthwise
1/2 cup blueberries
1/2 cup blackberries

Get ingredients: https://walmrt.us/3Bz29tG

Instructions:
1. Over medium heat, make simple syrup by combining 1 cup sugar with 1 cup water, & stir until dissolved. Remove to cool. 
2. Squeeze 3/4 cups lemon juice (about 6 large lemons) into a lidded glass jar (1 quart or larger). 
3. Add simple syrup and cold water to the jar, put the lid on, & shake to mix. 
4. Prepare fruits for popsicles & set out popsicle mold(s). 
To make the Fresh Medley Popsicles, layer peach, kiwi, & strawberry slices into popsicle molds, & fill any holes with blueberries along the way. Pour in lemonade to top of molds, then place top & sticks, & freeze 4-8 hours. 
For Tropical Fruit Popsicles, repeat, using pineapple, mango, & honeydew slices instead of peach, kiwi, & strawberries. For Berry Lover Popsicles, repeat, using strawberries, blackberries, & blueberries. 
5. Once popsicles are ready, remove from molds, & serve immediately. If popsicles are stuck in the molds, run under warm water for 10 seconds before removing.

mzMNT3xnve0.title: Calling All Entrepreneurs
mzMNT3xnve0.description: Jenny Dalquist‚Äôs grandfather came back to the United States from WWII with a background in metal working and chemistry, and her grandmother couldn‚Äôt find a lot of the products she used to cook her favorite Scandinavian dishes. Together they opened a family business in the Minneapolis area back in 1946 called Nordic Ware. After responding to Mr. Sam‚Äôs call for American manufacturers, Nordic Ware‚Äôs signature Bundt pan landed on our store shelves in 1986. Decades later they are now one of our longtime suppliers selling dozens of items, and John Furner recently toured their factory in person. We made a commitment earlier this year to spend an additional $350 billion on items made, grown or assembled in the U.S., and as we kick off our 8th annual Open Call this week, companies like Nordic Ware are what it‚Äôs all about. We welcome entrepreneurs from all over the country to virtually present their products to our merchandise buyers for a chance to get started with Walmart, just like Jenny‚Äôs family. Listen to this new episode of The Huddle with John Furner to hear their story.

NFo9cvbrHL4.title: Working at Walmart: Our People Make the Difference
NFo9cvbrHL4.description: Our people make the difference, and Teresa Machuca and Linda Truong are great examples of that. When Linda first started working at Walmart at Store 2066 in Houston, Texas, as a pharmacist, she met Teresa. Teresa was a cashier at the time and said she wanted to become a pharmacy technician to help her Hispanic community. Linda supported Teresa and encouraged her to achieve her goal. When Teresa lost her grandmother due to COVID-19, she made it her mission to protect the people she loves, taking time to educate her bilingual and Spanish-speaking customers, friends and family about the importance of vaccinations. We‚Äôre grateful Teresa and Linda are part of our Walmart family and glad you get to hear from them in this new episode of ‚ÄúThe Huddle‚Äù with John Furner.

H1EBF9FQqng.title: Grilled Peach Pizza Recipe | Chow Down with Walmart ‚Äã
H1EBF9FQqng.description:
Switch up your routine & freshen up pizza with peaches off the grill! This delicious pie is topped with gooey mozzarella, cherry tomatoes, & grilled peaches. Go ahead & add some prosciutto & basil to really impress your fam with your culinary skills. Love it? Hit subscribe for more Chow Down goodness!

Ingredients:
1 (13.8 oz) tube pizza dough
All-purpose flour for dusting
Canola oil
2 medium peaches
3/4 cup mixed cherry tomatoes
8 oz fresh mozzarella, sliced
4 oz prosciutto, thin sliced (optional)
Extra virgin olive oil
1/4 cup basil leaves, torn (optional)
Sea salt, to taste
Parchment paper 

Get ingredients: https://walmrt.us/3xbjV3D

Instructions:

1. Preheat your grill or oven to 425 degrees. If using an oven, place an upside down sheet tray inside to serve as a pizza stone. 
2. Preheat grill or grill pan to medium-high. Unroll the pizza dough onto a lightly floured surface. Tuck under the corners & roll out into a 16x9 inch rectangle. 
3. Brush your grill or hot grill pan with canola oil & lay down dough to grill- 5 minutes on first side, then flip & cook 2 min. Remove to parchment topped sheet tray. 
4. Halve each peach, remove pit, then cut into 6 wedges. Brush grill or grill pan with oil again & add peaches- grill flesh side down for 2-3 minutes on each side until tender. 
5. Tear mozzarella & add to grilled crust. Halve cherry tomatoes, then add to crust with cheese. Holding the parchment paper underneath, slide & transfer the pizza onto the grill, or hot preheated sheet tray inside the oven. Grill with cover on, or bake at 425 degrees for 6-8 minutes, cheese should be melted.
6. Remove pizza from grill or oven, top with the grilled peaches. Optional: tear prosciutto slices into smaller pieces & add to pizza, then top with basil leaves. Finish with a drizzle of olive oil & sea salt. Cut into 12 squares & serve.

Follow us on TikTok: https://walmrt.us/3zZbSIS

Cheddar Apple Grilled Cheese Sandwich Ingredients:

Empanada Pack Ingredients:
1 package Great Value already pulled chicken
1/2 bag mini red potatoes, diced small
1/2 tsp. each salt & pepper
1 jar Great Value white corn & black bean salsa
2 Great Value pie crust, cut in half

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

Cajun Pack Ingredients:

Ingredients:

FKEZahe-22Q.title: Raviolio Lasagna: 5-Ingredient Inspirations
FKEZahe-22Q.description:
You‚Äôre only five ingredients away from feeding your family a ravioli lasagna they‚Äôll love more & more with every bite. Walmart Chef Suzanne Clark makes preparing delicious meals easier than ever. Who‚Äôs the best chef around? It‚Äôs about to be you! üíÅüèΩ‚Äç Subscribe now & learn how to please even the pickiest eaters in your household.

Ingredients:
1 Great Value mild ground Italian sausage, 16 oz.
1 frozen Great Value cheese ravioli pasta, 25 oz.
2 Great Value tomato basil garlic sauce, 24 oz.
1 Great Value finely shredded low-moisture part-skim mozzarella, 16 oz.
1 Great Value finely shredded parmesan cheese, 6 oz.

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees & spray a 9x13 baking dish with Great Value cooking spray.
2. Place sausage in a large pan over medium heat, & cook to 165 degrees. Drain off excess fat, & add sauce to the pan.
3. To begin lasagna, spoon 1/3 of meat sauce into the bottom of the pan.
4. Arrange frozen ravioli evenly to start the first layer. Sprinkle with ¬Ω of the mozzarella cheese, & half of the parmesan cheese.
5. Repeat the above step for the second layer. Cover with foil & bake for 40 minutes.
6. Remove foil, & continue baking for 15 minutes or until the top is golden & the sauce is bubbly. Let cool for at least 10 minutes before serving.

Chef tip: Please note, ravioli needs to be added frozen, no need to cook first! For additional flavor & a gourmet touch, you can add your favorite fresh herbs such as Italian parsley, basil, or oregano. Sprinkle on the top, or add to the sauce before assembling.

sWGDCqf8AFE.title: Asian-inspired Lettuce Wraps | Chow Down with Walmart‚Äã
sWGDCqf8AFE.description:

Pro tip: Once you've perfected these Asian-inspired faves, swap out new ingredients to keep everyone coming back for more. Don't forget to subscribe for more Chow Down hits!

Ingredients:
Sauce:
3 Tbsp. soy sauce 
3 Tbsp. hoisin sauce 
1 Tbsp. sesame oil
1 Tbsp. rice wine vinegar
1 Tbsp. honey
2 tsp. sweet chili sauce 
1/2 tsp. garlic powder
1/4 tsp. powdered ginger

Lettuce wraps:
1 rotisserie chicken
1 Tbsp. avocado oil
1/2 onion, minced
1 cup red pepper, diced
1 8 oz can water chestnuts, drained & minced
Half a bag of cauliflower rice
Bean sprouts
Butter lettuce

Garnish:
Crush peanuts
Wonton strips

Directions:
Whisk together sauce ingredients until well combined. 
Shred the rotisserie chicken.
Heat avocado oil in a frying pan. Add onion & cook for 5 minutes or until the onion becomes translucent.
Add the peppers, water chestnuts, cauliflower, & bean sprouts, cook about 5 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add sauce & shredded chicken & simmer on low heat until everything is evenly coated & heated through.
Serve in lettuce leaves, on top of your favorite Asian salad, or over noodles or rice! Garnish with crushed peanuts & wonton strips.

‚ÄãIngredients:
1-2 lb skirt steak
2 tbsp Hershey‚Äôs Cocoa powder
1 tbsp Great Value salt
3 tbsp Great Value olive oil
1 tsp Great Value chipotle powder
1 tsp Great Value garlic powder
2 tbsp Great Value brown sugar

‚ÄãChipotle Kiss Barbeque Sauce
1‚ÅÑ4 cup Hershey‚Äôs Kisses (Melted)
2 cups Great Value Original Barbeque Sauce
1‚ÅÑ2 tsp Great Value chipotle powder

‚ÄãInstructions:
1. Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. In a bowl, combine chili powder, salt, pepper, garlic, cocoa, and brown sugar. In a separate bowl, combine barbeque sauce, chipotle powder, and melted kisses, set aside for later use.

4. Serve steak with Chipotle Kiss Barbeque Sauce.

¬Ω cup Great Value cocoa

ouOf4utnH8E.description:
‚ÄúPumpkin Bars happen to be one of my all-time favorite desserts, and this one is super easy to make!‚Äù 

Get a downloadable recipe card: ‚Äãhttps://bit.ly/3mCG1Gz

Get ingredients: ‚Äãhttps://bit.ly/3boARIc

Hershey‚Äôs Pumpkin Bars Ingredients:
1 cup pumpkin puree
1 teaspoon Great Value organic pumpkin pie spice 1‚ÅÑ2 teaspoon baking soda
1‚ÅÑ2 teaspoon baking powder
11/2 cups all purpose flour
1‚ÅÑ2 teaspoon salt
1 stick of butter, melted
1 cup sugar
1 egg
1‚ÅÑ2 teaspoon vanilla
Toppings: Heath Bits

Hershey‚Äôs Pumpkin Bars Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 350¬∞F and line a small cookie sheet with parchment paper.
2. Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, and salt together in a large bowl. Set aside.
3. In a separate bowl, whisk pumpkin puree, butter, sugar, egg, and vanilla until combined. Pour the dry ingredients into the bowl and mix well.
4. Bake for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and cool bars completely.
5. Pour Hershey‚Äôs milk chocolate glaze on top of the bars and spread with a spatula. Top with a generous amount of heath bits. Cut into squares and serve.
